# lsearch-fetch - Fetch URL to Knowledge Base

Download a web page and add it to the knowledge base.

## Usage

```
/lsearch-fetch <url> [title]
```

## Arguments

- `url` (required): URL to fetch
- `title` (optional): Custom title for the document

## Examples

```bash
# Fetch API documentation
/lsearch-fetch https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

# Fetch with custom title
/lsearch-fetch https://api.example.com/docs "Example API Docs"
```

## Supported Formats

- HTML documentation (converted to Markdown)
- Swagger/OpenAPI JSON specs
- Plain text
